<!-- wp:create-block/kateandtoms-reviews {"reviews":[{"review":"Fourteen of our family from age three to seventy-five got together for a celebration of my husband's birthday at Marsden Manor and enjoyed the most wonderful weekend in this beautiful place. We all want to go back and are trying to think of an excuse for a celebration next year! We made full use of the croquet, tennis , table tennis, swimming pool, two TV rooms, little ones playroom , Wendy house, and all the games. Bensons delivered a most welcome meal for our first evening, and served a superb buffet lunch on the Sunday. A truly magical weekend!","reviewer":"Stephanie"},{"review":"We had a wonderful time at Marsden Manor. The children loved the pool, media room and exploring the vast gardens. My youngest would simply not leave the Wendy house! We cannot wait to return.","reviewer":"Fiona"},{"review":"Thank you kate u0026amp; tom's for helping us book Marsden Manor for our anniversary. The house is simply stunning with everything we could have possibly asked for for a wonderful weekend.","reviewer":"Hayley"},{"review":"It was a privilege to spend a few days at Marsden Manor. It is a beautifully decorated and thoughtfully appointed grand home set in the rolling Costwolds hills. Swimming pool, tennis court, croquet lawn, table tennis, walking trails setting out from the back of the property, a beer brewery a stone's throw away and even a selection of kids toys and games kept us all occupied during our stay. Kate u0026amp; Tom's made sure our every comfort was catered for without intruding in any way.","reviewer":"Matt"},{"review":"We had a wonderful stay at Marsden Manor. The house and gardens were beautiful and immaculately maintained. We were welcomed on arrival by Diana, and an offering of fresh eggs, bread and home made jam. The beds were fantastic. Fluffy towels. Plentiful pool towels, tennis racquets and a wealth of games to keep the children entertained.","reviewer":"Isabella"},{"review":"We were a party of 19 who stayed at Marsden Manor to celebrate my wife's 50th birthday. The house, grounds, facilities and location were sensational. We were welcomed by Diana, who gave a very thorough briefing as to where everything was and was on call throughout the weekend, should we need anything else. There was easily enough room for 19 people to lose themselves and very easy access to a walk up the hill behind, to enjoy the views of the beautiful countryside. All 19 of us would thoroughly recommend Marsden Manor to anyone. Thank you.u0022","reviewer":"Ben"},{"review":"The entire team had a fantastic time thank you. They all loved the facilities such as the table tennis, tennis court, swimming pool and pool table.The house and grounds were amazing, Diana was also so lovely showing us around (she even made us a cake to welcome the team.)","reviewer":"Steve"},{"review":"Marsden Manor is fantastic. A truly beautiful house. Plenty of indoor space, amazing gardens and a fabulous pool. Our entire party had a ball of a weekend.","reviewer":"Tracy"},{"review":"We rented Marsden Manor for a big family celebration, its 10 super-sized, super-king bedrooms and 7 bathrooms were perfect for our group of 14. Ages ranged from 4 to 70 yrs. The elegantly furnished drawing room and other two sitting rooms gave everyone plenty of space to relax and play board games, warmed by crackling log-fires. However, there wasn't much time for board games, after playing pool, table tennis, tennis and enjoying the beautifully heated and covered swimming pool or enjoying the beautiful gardens. I can thoroughly recommend kate u0026amp; tom's, they have a pleasant, totally professional team. Communications are clear and detailed, any queries answered without delay. We were greeted at the Manor by Diana, who gave us a very comprehensive tour and was available to call at any time during our stay if needed, she wasn't.","reviewer":"Michael"},{"review":"We had the most wonderful time at Marsden manor with our family celebrating our 60th wedding anniversary.  The manor had everything to keep the whole family entertained from our 1 year old right up to ourselves and every one in between. Thanks to Diana who organised everything and special thanks to Lucy and her team for the amazing food she prepared for us. I wouldn't hesitate to recommend them.","reviewer":"Maureen"},{"review":"Homely feel for family group. Great indoor and outdoor facilities. Privacy and spacious grounds with glorious Cotswold views.","reviewer":"Vin u0026 Marianne"},{"review":"I recently stayed at Marsden Manor, managed by kate and tom's, and it was a fantastic experience. The house was beautiful and the customer service was amazing. The staff went above and beyond to ensure our comfort and satisfaction. I highly recommend kate and tom's for a luxurious and memorable getaway.","reviewer":"Daniel"},{"review":"This is the most wonderful house to accommodate 20 people comfortably. The house u0026 gardens were a delight to relax in u0026 the pool top notch. Everyone loved being at Marsden Manor!","reviewer":"Amanda"},{"review":"We had a wonderful week at Marsden Manor - 10 adults and 6 children ranging in age from 9 months to 9 years. A beautiful house, with so much space for everyone and with lovely gardens. The children all loved the swimming pool, which was heated to a very warm temperature.","reviewer":"Jane"},{"review":"Great place. Beautiful grounds  All rooms lovely which is unusual in such a large property","reviewer":"Jen"}],"textAlign":"center","reviewFontSize":"0.875rem","reviewerFontSize":"0.875rem","align":"wide"} -->
<div class="wp-block-create-block-kateandtoms-reviews alignwide has-text-align-center"><div class="reviews-container"><div class="review-item" data-index="0"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">Fourteen of our family from age three to seventy-five got together for a celebration of my husband&#039;s birthday at Marsden Manor and enjoyed the most wonderful weekend in this beautiful place. We all want to go back and are trying to think of an excuse for a celebration next year! We made full use of the croquet, tennis , table tennis, swimming pool, two TV rooms, little ones playroom , Wendy house, and all the games. Bensons delivered a most welcome meal for our first evening, and served a superb buffet lunch on the Sunday. A truly magical weekend!</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Stephanie</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="1"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">We had a wonderful time at Marsden Manor. The children loved the pool, media room and exploring the vast gardens. My youngest would simply not leave the Wendy house! We cannot wait to return.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Fiona</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="2"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">Thank you kate u0026amp; tom&#039;s for helping us book Marsden Manor for our anniversary. The house is simply stunning with everything we could have possibly asked for for a wonderful weekend.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Hayley</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="3"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">It was a privilege to spend a few days at Marsden Manor. It is a beautifully decorated and thoughtfully appointed grand home set in the rolling Costwolds hills. Swimming pool, tennis court, croquet lawn, table tennis, walking trails setting out from the back of the property, a beer brewery a stone&#039;s throw away and even a selection of kids toys and games kept us all occupied during our stay. Kate u0026amp; Tom&#039;s made sure our every comfort was catered for without intruding in any way.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Matt</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="4"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">We had a wonderful stay at Marsden Manor. The house and gardens were beautiful and immaculately maintained. We were welcomed on arrival by Diana, and an offering of fresh eggs, bread and home made jam. The beds were fantastic. Fluffy towels. Plentiful pool towels, tennis racquets and a wealth of games to keep the children entertained.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Isabella</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="5"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">We were a party of 19 who stayed at Marsden Manor to celebrate my wife&#039;s 50th birthday. The house, grounds, facilities and location were sensational. We were welcomed by Diana, who gave a very thorough briefing as to where everything was and was on call throughout the weekend, should we need anything else. There was easily enough room for 19 people to lose themselves and very easy access to a walk up the hill behind, to enjoy the views of the beautiful countryside. All 19 of us would thoroughly recommend Marsden Manor to anyone. Thank you.&quot;</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Ben</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="6"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">The entire team had a fantastic time thank you. They all loved the facilities such as the table tennis, tennis court, swimming pool and pool table.The house and grounds were amazing, Diana was also so lovely showing us around (she even made us a cake to welcome the team.)</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Steve</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="7"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">Marsden Manor is fantastic. A truly beautiful house. Plenty of indoor space, amazing gardens and a fabulous pool. Our entire party had a ball of a weekend.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Tracy</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="8"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">We rented Marsden Manor for a big family celebration, its 10 super-sized, super-king bedrooms and 7 bathrooms were perfect for our group of 14. Ages ranged from 4 to 70 yrs. The elegantly furnished drawing room and other two sitting rooms gave everyone plenty of space to relax and play board games, warmed by crackling log-fires. However, there wasn&#039;t much time for board games, after playing pool, table tennis, tennis and enjoying the beautifully heated and covered swimming pool or enjoying the beautiful gardens. I can thoroughly recommend kate u0026amp; tom&#039;s, they have a pleasant, totally professional team. Communications are clear and detailed, any queries answered without delay. We were greeted at the Manor by Diana, who gave us a very comprehensive tour and was available to call at any time during our stay if needed, she wasn&#039;t.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Michael</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="9"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">We had the most wonderful time at Marsden manor with our family celebrating our 60th wedding anniversary.  The manor had everything to keep the whole family entertained from our 1 year old right up to ourselves and every one in between. Thanks to Diana who organised everything and special thanks to Lucy and her team for the amazing food she prepared for us. I wouldn&#039;t hesitate to recommend them.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Maureen</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="10"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">Homely feel for family group. Great indoor and outdoor facilities. Privacy and spacious grounds with glorious Cotswold views.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Vin & Marianne</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="11"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">I recently stayed at Marsden Manor, managed by kate and tom&#039;s, and it was a fantastic experience. The house was beautiful and the customer service was amazing. The staff went above and beyond to ensure our comfort and satisfaction. I highly recommend kate and tom&#039;s for a luxurious and memorable getaway.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Daniel</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="12"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">This is the most wonderful house to accommodate 20 people comfortably. The house &amp; gardens were a delight to relax in &amp; the pool top notch. Everyone loved being at Marsden Manor!</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Amanda</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="13"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">We had a wonderful week at Marsden Manor - 10 adults and 6 children ranging in age from 9 months to 9 years. A beautiful house, with so much space for everyone and with lovely gardens. The children all loved the swimming pool, which was heated to a very warm temperature.</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Jane</cite></div><div class="review-item" data-index="14"><blockquote class="review-text" style="font-size:0.875rem">Great place. Beautiful grounds  All rooms lovely which is unusual in such a large property</blockquote><cite class="reviewer-name" style="font-size:0.875rem">Jen</cite></div></div></div>
